              "pageContent": "EditionShould you go electric?The future of electric travelYour EV questions, answeredBecoming ID.Fully charged eventTiny BuzzVolkswagen Stories: Timo ThorntonID. Buzz Artwork WrapVolkswagen Social HubVolkswagen MerchandiseNewsLooking after your Volkswagen electric vehicleBook an electric serviceHomeElectric and hybrid carsLiving electricLooking after your EVMaintenance of a Volkswagen electric vehicle is simpler than its combustion engine counterpart as it has fewer components.Taking care of your Volkswagen electric vehicle couldn’t be easier![Technician reviewing his checklist in front of an electric car](https://assets.volkswagen.com/is/image/volkswagenag/looking_after_your-ev-less_to_worry-16x9-1920x1080?Zml0PWNyb3AsMSZmbXQ9anBnJnFsdD03OSZ3aWQ9ODAwJmhlaT00NTAmYWxpZ249MC4wMCwwLjAwJmJmYz1vZmYmNjYwMA==)Less to worry aboutNo spark plugs to be replaced. No oil to be changed. No exhaust to repair. No vulnerable components such as a cam belt, clutch or gearbox.![Technician diagnosing an",
