        {
          "content": "Where can I charge a Volkswagen ID.? And how much does it cost?",
          "role": "user",
          "time": "2024-10-25T15:26:53.092Z"
        },
        {
          "content": "You can charge your Volkswagen ID vehicle at various public charging stations throughout the UK, easily found using the We Connect ID. app, which also allows you to plan routes with recommended charging stops. As for the costs, they can vary depending on the charging network and your chosen tariff. For up-to-date information on charging costs, please visit https://www.volkswagen.co.uk/en/electric-and-hybrid/charging-and-range/charging/running-costs.html.",
          "role": "bot",
          "time": "2024-10-25T15:26:57.561Z",
          "sourceDocuments": [
            {
              "pageContent": "The charging process at the charging stations can be started practically using the We Charge charging card or via the We Connect ID. app.1.An offer from Volkswagen Group Charging GmbH (Elli).2.More than 80% of the available European public charging infrastructure.Need helpCareersInfo for emergency respondersContact UsNewsLoginTechnologyConnected servicesPrivacyCompliance and IntegrityLegalFAQsFind a retailerManage cookiesID. Import NoticeVolkswagen AG (Imprint & Legal texts)Important information :^If you are selecting a Volkswagen ID.3, ID.4, ID.5, ID.7, ID.7 Tourer or ID.Buzz then prices shown are the MDP (Manufacturer's Direct Price). This is the price set by Volkswagen which you pay for the vehicle. Volkswagen ID vehicles are sold by Volkswagen UK, a trading division of Volkswagen Group United Kingdom Limited (please note that you will need to visit an authorised Volkswagen Retailer (acting as agent for Volkswagen UK) to order, purchase and take delivery of your Volkswagen ID",
              "metadata": {
                "loc.lines.from": 396,
                "loc.lines.to": 396,
                "source": "https://www.volkswagen.co.uk/en/electric-and-hybrid/electric-cars/id4.html/__layer/layers/content_slider/id_4/tech/charging-on-the-move/master.layer"
              }
            },
            {
              "pageContent": "with your Volkswagen ID. model is now even more convenient: with Plug & Charge, the new standard for convenient charging. All you need is the ID. software 3.1 or higher, the We Connect ID. app plus a Plug & Charge-enabled We Charge rate. Then you simply pull up at the Plug & Charge charging station, activate Plug & Charge via the app and in the vehicle and plug in the charging cable. The\"},{\"kind\":\"htmlElement\",\"tagName\":\"b\",\"children\":\\[{\"kind\":\"textNode\",\"value\":\" registration, charging and invoicing \"}\\]},{\"kind\":\"textNode\",\"value\":\"are all automatic. Then you continue your drive and",
              "metadata": {
                "loc.lines.from": 347,
                "loc.lines.to": 347,
                "source": "https://www.volkswagen.co.uk/en/electric-and-hybrid/electric-cars/id3.html/__layer/layers/content_slider/the_new_id_3/technical_functions/plug---charge/master.layer"
              }
            },
            {
              "pageContent": "We Charge Volkswagen offers you the fitting solution for charging your ID.4 in public when on the go. Remarkably simple to use via the We Connect ID. app, you can find available charging stations nearby, plan routes with automatic charging stop recommendations and automatically pay for your charging via your We Charge charging tariff\"},{\"kind\":\"disclaimer\",\"disclaimers\":\\[{\"displayType\":\"T4\\_ITEM\\_BASED\",\"text\":\"An offer from Volkswagen Group Charging GmbH (Elli).\",\"id\":\"DIS\\_134\",\"numericId\":\"DISN\\_145\"}\\]},{\"kind\":\"textNode\",\"value\":\" – including monthly billing and complete cost control. Throughout Europe you have access to approx. 150,000 charging points\"},{\"kind\":\"disclaimer\",\"disclaimers\":\\[{\"displayType\":\"T4\\_ITEM\\_BASED\",\"text\":\"More than 80% of the available European public charging infrastructure.\",\"id\":\"DIS\\_135\",\"numericId\":\"DISN\\_146\"}\\]},{\"kind\":\"textNode\",\"value\":\" including the whole IONITY quick charging network, which offers varying preferential terms depending on",
              "metadata": {
                "loc.lines.from": 347,
                "loc.lines.to": 347,
                "source": "https://www.volkswagen.co.uk/en/electric-and-hybrid/electric-cars/id4.html/__layer/layers/content_slider/id_4/tech/charging-on-the-move/master.layer"
              }
            },
            {
              "pageContent": "battery technology has evolved massively over the last few years. If you use your car, like most drivers, to run errands, for the school run or to drive to work you probably average less than 19.5 miles per day. Which means you’ll only need to fully charge once every couple of weeks. Longer journeys are fine too, 280 - 435 miles is the range our IDs are now hitting.![Close-up of person charging their ID.3](https://assets.volkswagen.com/is/image/volkswagenag/electric_cars-the_new_id3_2023-IN0272_ID3_exterior_charging_plug-16x9-1920x1152?Zml0PWNyb3AsMSZmbXQ9anBnJnFsdD03OSZ3aWQ9ODAwJmhlaT00ODAmYWxpZ249MC4wMCwwLjAwJmJmYz1vZmYmZGI2OQ==)Charging optionsYou can charge your Volkswagen electric vehicle with a 3-pin plug. This is the slowest method but basically means you can charge anywhere there’s electricity. What we recommend is that you install an Ohme wallbox, which allows you to fully charge quicker and easier. Since December 2022 the public charging network has grown by 45%. Zapmap",
              "metadata": {
                "loc.lines.from": 356,
                "loc.lines.to": 356,
                "source": "https://www.volkswagen.co.uk/en/electric-and-hybrid/living-electric/lifestyle.html"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
